posts_info.description: 😒They didn’t have to do me like that! 😭 A little backstory: When I was younger, I wanted to be a singer. Watching Beyoncé and Rihanna, I just knew that was what I was meant to do! I was always in the choir and even forced my parents to pay for private voice lessons. I would practice every day for years. One day, I just accepted the fact that singing was not a talent God gave me. We all know that people with raspy voices are the best singers, so when I got sick and started losing my voice, I thought maybe now I would be able to sing. So, I sat my family down like I used to when I was younger and asked them to listen to me sing. Except now I’m a lot older, so they have no problem hurting my feelings. Whereas before, they would listen to me and tell me I’m getting better, now they laugh hysterically! 😫😭

Overall, I think the kids haa a good Christmas season!  Ready for new years!  #christmas #momlife #kids

Merry Christmas Friends! 🎁🎄  This season was a success! My daughter and niece are so special to me and im just happy I have the possibility to show them how loved they are beyond measure!  Have a wonderful Christmas today celebrating the birth of Jesus. May today be filled with an overwhelming amount of joy!  If today is hard for you, I am very sorry. Some seasons are harder than others. As content creators we often show the best parts of ourselves but just know everyone has low seasons as well and this too shall pass. Cast all of your burdens on Jesus Christ and know that it is just a season. You will come out the other side stronger and more alive and tou will look back at this season and have a story to tell!  Love you! ❤️

Leaving was the best thing I ever did… I worked in corporate America for 11 years before taking leave to take care of my children. The child care system failed me and my family and I couldn’t stand barely seeing my children anymore. Something had to change.  How did I do it? Before I left work I started selling my old items on Poshmark to make extra money. I quickly realized I could make money off of items I found at thrift stores, estate sales, and yard sales. I could feel this would be something that was going to be what helped me and my family through this tough time. At first it was nice to have something while the kids were at school but then I found my business growing! Here is what it did for me! Reselling gives you:  ✅ flexibility  ✅ good pay  ✅ No one to answer to but yourself <— that’s my favorite one 😂 ✅ Unlimited earnings  ✅ And did I mention flexibility!?!  Follow me as I share my story to help out other that may feel stuck and looking for new way to do things! I share daily tips and experiences in my reselling journey and what it has provided for me and my family! Now you can make Mozzarella Cheese at home 🧀  Recipe ⬇️ RECETA ⬇️ Very easy 2 ingredient mozzarella cheese so you can make at home. So simple and delicious! ☺️🧀 Está receta solo ocupa 2 ingredientes🫶🏼  Recipe: • 5 liters of raw cow’s milk or low-temp pasteurized whole milk. You can NOT use ultra pasteurized milk.  • 200 ml of vinegar (I used white) • Heat milk to 46° C , take off heat, add vinegar, stir to combine for about 25 seconds, cover with lid and leave for 10 minutes.  • remove cheese curds from the liquid whey and shape into balls. Squeeze out as much whey as possible.  • heat whey back up to 65° C and add the balls of mozzarella back in for 30 second increments each. Take out and stretch until it becomes stretchy and smooth. Do this about 3-5 times until nice and smooth.  • Shape into balls and add salt if you’d like  • place balls into room temp or iced whey/water in the fridge for up to 1 week Enjoy☺️  RECETA: • 5 litros de leche de vaca cruda o leche entera pasteurizada a baja temperatura  • 200 ml de vinagre blanco • Calienta la leche hasta que alcance una temperatura de 46° C, remueve del fuego, agrega el vinagre, mezcla por unos 25 segundos. cubrir con tapa y déjalo por 10 minutos.  • retire la cuajada de queso del suero de leche. Darle forma de bolas. exprime la mayor cantidad de líquido posible  • calienta el suero de leche a 65° C y agrega las bolas de mozzarella por 30 segundos cada uno. Saca y estira hasta que quede elástico y suave. Repite este proceso 3-5 veces. Hasta que todas las bolas estén bien suaves.  • formar bolas con el queso y añade sal  • guardar el queso mozzarella a temperatura ambiente o en agua helada/ suero helada en la nevera hasta por una semana  #mozzarella #mozzarellacheese #homemadecheese #gabrielavlogs #gabrielamkv #cheeserecipes #EasyRecipes #Recipe #recetas #queso #quesomozzarella #quesocasero

posts_info.description: 5 cleaning mistakes you may be making! 🫣   1)    Not letting the product sit to penetrate the germs long enough: If you are wiping up right away, then you aren’t letting the product do its job and eat up the grime while disinfecting! 2)    Using too much product in mop bucket or not wringing out your mop enough 💧: If your floors are ending up streaky, it means the mop head has too much water on it (wring it out better) and if the floors come out cloudy, then you have put too much product in the bucket 🪣 3)    Not vacuuming carpet in cross direction: If you are only vacuuming one direction and not flipping and vacuuming sideways/the other direction afterwards, you aren’t getting deep into the carpet fibers and picking everything up! 🧵 4)    Not dusting or vacuuming surfaces first: ensuring you are dusting or using a soft haired brush to vacuum dirt and debris before wiping any surface is very important to ensure you aren’t just adding water to dirt and creating mud in your home! 🧽 5)    Not Maintaining Your Cleaning Machines: Make sure you be cleaning and maintaining your cleaning machines and rags properly, so that you can extend the lifetime of them! 🧼We will go over maintaining and cleaning machines during our spring cleaning segment coming up! 🌷     Are you making any of these mistakes?!     Follow for more cleaning tips!   Products 🔗 in Amazon Shop in B | 0, see the “as seen in videos” list❤️  #cleaningtiktok #CleanTok #cleaningtips #cleaningmistakes #cleaning

The best home hacks of 2022! Thank you all for making this year so incredibly amazing I am thrilled to share my favorite home hacks that were posted this year! Follow along fore more ❤️✨ #homehacks #lifehacks #organizationhacks #cleaninghacks #CleanTok

👇🏻SEE WHY HERE 👇🏻 The REAL reason you home is causing you stress is NOT because of a lack of time, space, or the people in it, it's… 😱CLUTTER😱 Psychologists say that VISUAL CLUTTER can cause equal amounts of stress on the mind, body, AND space…..So that messy room isn’t just a physical weight… but a mental one too! 😱 Let’s dive in deeper! 🤿 1️⃣ Visual Noise Overload 🧠: Feel mentally exhausted in a cluttered room? It's not just you! 😶‍🌫️ Research shows visual clutter overwhelms the brain with excessive stimuli, making it hard for your brain to process, focus & relax. 🌪️ 2️⃣ Cortisol Chaos 🌪️: Your body's stress alarm, cortisol, goes haywire in a messy space! 📉😱 Studies prove that elevated cortisol levels are linked to chronic stress, anxiety, & even potential long-term health issues.🌿🧘‍♀️ 3️⃣ Control Matters 🎮: Feeling helpless in a messy space? 🛟 That’s because a disorganized space can trigger a sense of losing control. 🫨 ‼️Chaotic & Disorganized Space ﹦ Losing Control ≠ CALM ‼️ 4️⃣ Task Troubles 📋: Clutter isn't just in your way; it's blocking your mental pathways! 🚧 A cluttered space hinders your ability to do tasks that require concentration & focus. 🧹💡 This can create severe frustration & stress! 😱 5️⃣ Unfinished Business: Messy spaces are like nagging to-do lists. Every pile is a reminder of unfinished tasks. 📋 6️⃣ Order = Joy: It's not just about appearance. A tidy space triggers a positive brain response! 🌈 When cleaning/organizing, the brain perceives a sense of order & accomplishment (& positive mood)!😁 ‼️ READY to destress and transform your space into a haven? ‼️ FOLLOW US & join us for our “Decluttering Dash, 15 Min Task” Challenge on IG& FB stories all of January 2024 ✨ ❤️ We will help you declutter your home, in just 15 min a day with daily tasks! ❤️ Find me in stories to discover how a tidy home, means a happier you! 😍 #declutteringtips #declutteryourhome #declutteryourlife #declutterchallenge #declutteringfacts

Home hack: Remove hard water and soap scum from your glass shower! ✨ If you are constantly battling with hard water stains on your glass shower, or build up of soap scum, even after washing it! Try this!! Grab a magic eraser or generic melamine sponge (same thing just generic brand). Wipe your damp glass until all marks are removed. Rinse well 🚿 to remove all build up and spots. I love my detachable shower head for this (linked in my Amazon shop). Squeegee dry!!! ‼️Remember to do this after EVERY SHOWER to avoid build up and spots ‼️ If you still need extra shine, grab one of these lint free microfiber rags, and wipe with just water or with glass cleaner (inside and outside). Removing any remaining gunk and allowing to stay clean for longer! 🚿😍 All products linked in my Amazon shop in bio (see: “as seen in video” list or “bathroom favorite” list) ❤️ #bathroomcleaning #bathroom #showercleaning #bathroomclean #showerclean #deepclean #springclean #springcleaning #cleaninghacks #cleaningtips #cleaningmotivation #hardwaterstain

🎲 My game closet gave me ANXIETY! 😥 Originally Everything was piled in here, I couldn’t even see half the stuff we had, but who cares cause we couldn’t reach it anyways….. 🙃 ✨find these products in my Amazon Shop, linked in my bio (see list: “Extra Storage & Organization Favorites”) ❤️ 👏🏻 Let’s fix it…. 👏🏻 After I removed all the games, I wiped down the cabinets with my dusting sponge… & BOY was it gross 🤢! I got rid of any games we no longer played 🃏, which could have been all of them because we couldn’t reach them anyways 🙊…. , but once I had only the ones we wanted to keep, I tossed all the boxes and moved the games into these super handy organization baggies with labels. 🏷️ ⭐️ The first thing my husband says was “you didn’t write ‘puzzle’ on those”…. 😡 apparently the 1000 pieces in the bag didn’t give away what kind of game it was. 🤷🏼♀️ Just kidding, I love him!! ❤️ 📦 This process reduced the space all those wasted boxes took up and allowed me to make them astatically pleasing. 😍 Then I grabbed a few bins and popped the bags in there to keep them upright and together! posts_info.description: If you’ve got water, oil, and food coloring you can do this fun “fireworks” in a jar experiment today! 🎆 Save this post and read the instructions and tips below! Happy New Years, my friends! ❤️ WHAT YOU’LL NEED: Clear glass or jar Water Cooking oil (vegetable or baby oil) Liquid food coloring (various colors) Small dish Fork or stirrer HOW TO 1️⃣ Fill the glass about three-quarters full with water. 2️⃣ In a small dish, mix a few drops of liquid food coloring with a small amount of cooking oil. Stir gently to combine. 3️⃣ Pour the colored oil mixture into the glass of water. 4️⃣ Observe as the colored oil mixture disperses through the water, creating vibrant bursts of color. Pro Tip: don’t overmix the food coloring or pour the oil mixture into the glass too fast or else you may end up with a black glass of water!! THE SCIENCE  The Fireworks in a Jar experiment demonstrates the principle of immiscibility and varying densities of liquids, as the colored oil, being less dense than water, creates bursts of color like fireworks when introduced into the water-filled jar. #kidactivities #stemeducation #playideas #scienceexperimentsforkids #scienceforkids
